# DedgeAuth Consumer App UI Patterns

When adding or changing **modal dialogs** or **search history / search dialogs**, follow these standard patterns so tenant/fallback CSS applies consistently across all consumer apps.

## Modal Dialog Pattern

### HTML Structure

```html
<div class="modal-overlay hidden" id="myModal">
  <div class="modal-container modal-md">
    <div class="modal-header">
      <h2 class="modal-title">Dialog Title</h2>
      <button class="modal-close">&times;</button>
    </div>
    <div class="modal-body">
      <!-- Dialog content -->
    </div>
    <div class="modal-footer">
      <button class="btn btn-secondary" data-action="cancel">Cancel</button>
      <button class="btn btn-primary" data-action="confirm">Confirm</button>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```

### Size Classes on `.modal-container`

| Class | Width |
|-------|-------|
| `modal-sm` | 400px |
| `modal-md` | 600px |
| `modal-lg` | 900px |
| `modal-fullscreen` | Full viewport |

### Behavior

- Toggle visibility with class `hidden` or `active`/`show` on the overlay
- Close on: close button click, overlay click, Escape key
- Optionally trap focus and restore body scroll

### CSS Rule

Do **not** redefine `.modal-overlay`, `.modal-container`, `.modal-header`, `.modal-close`, `.modal-body`, `.modal-footer`, or the modal size classes in app-local CSS. These are provided by tenant/fallback theme.

## Search History Dropdown Pattern

### HTML Structure

```html
<div class="search-history-container">
  <button class="search-history-trigger">Recent</button>
  <div class="search-history-dropdown hidden">
    <div class="search-history-item">
      <span class="search-history-text">Previous search term</span>
      <span class="search-history-time">2 min ago</span>
    </div>
    <div class="search-history-empty">No recent searches</div>
    <button class="search-history-clear">Clear history</button>
  </div>
</div>
```

### Behavior

- Toggle dropdown visibility with `hidden` class
- Close on click outside the container

### CSS Rule

Do **not** redefine search-history classes in app CSS. These are provided by tenant/fallback theme.

## Reference Implementation

GenericLogHandler serves as the canonical reference:
- `wwwroot/log-search.html` -- search page with modal and history
- `wwwroot/js/components/modal.js` -- modal component
- `wwwroot/js/log-search.js` -- search with history
